== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From when babies have [[tantrum]]s, they spit out any [[dummy]] that they may be sucking.
=== Verb ===
'''[[spit]] [[the]] [[dummy]]'''
# {{idiom}} To overreact (as an adult) to a situation childishly, in an angry or frustrated manner.
#: ''He'll really '''spit the dummy''' when he hears that he's been fired...''
